This paper deals with distributed computing and consensus algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of graphs and iterative algorithms suggests a possible categorization under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the use of convex hulls and real vectors may also suggest a possible categorization under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
